<section class="api-section api-improve" aria-labelledby="api-improve-heading">
  <h1 class="api-page-title" id="api-improve-heading">Improve: the loop that compounds</h1>
  <p>
    Improvement runs under the same rules as the runtime: typed contracts, immutable receipts,
    fail-closed gates. Misses become measurement; nothing scores itself.
  </p>
  <p class="api-pipeline">
    run misses &rarr; mine &rarr; route (exclusive) &rarr; agent draft &rarr; blinded adjudication
    &rarr; freeze &rarr; pre-register &rarr; score &rarr; compare
  </p>

  <div class="api-improve-grid">
    <div class="api-improve-block">
      <h3>Exclusive routing</h3>
      <p>
        At mine time a clip feeds exactly one pool: the frozen bench, or the learning stream of
        glossary entries, rules, and correction pairs. Never both, recorded before adjudication,
        enforced at clip level. That is the price of an honest improvement curve.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="api-improve-block">
      <h3>The memory gate</h3>
      <p>
        Runs only propose. A different actor accepts, rejects, or revokes with a reason, and
        behavioral rules additionally require a pre-registered ablation pair on the same frozen
        pack. Nothing has passed the gate yet; a gate that never opened for weak evidence is the
        feature.
      </p>
      <p class="api-status">accepted_entries: 0 · legacy_quarantined: 1</p>
    </div>
    <div class="api-improve-block">
      <h3>Scored, honestly</h3>
      <p>
        One frozen pack, one scored run, and a prepped arm that scored below the cold control. The
        number is published on the <a href="/benchmarks/">benchmarks page</a> because the loop only
        works if misses are captured, not explained away.
      </p>
      <p class="api-status">packs_frozen: 1 · scored_runs: 1 · judge: null</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="api-improve-block api-improve-wide">
    <h3>The declared next tier: offline adapters</h3>
    <p>
      Today accepted memory conditions runs through retrieval. The declared next rung exports
      adjudicated correction pairs into offline adapter training, under a contract fixed before any
      adapter exists:
    </p>
    <ul class="api-list">
      <li>All learning is offline over journaled receipts. Nothing learns inside a run.</li>
      <li>
        The correction row schema is already the training row shape; provenance-clean pairs come
        only from the learning-routed pool, never from bench clips.
      </li>
      <li>
        Weight training waits until the adjudicated pair count clears roughly one thousand. Current
        yield is about five rows per run, so this rung is measured in months.
      </li>
      <li>
        A trained adapter ships as a versioned, content-addressed policy artifact behind the same
        proposal-to-decision gate as a rule, accepted only through a pre-registered ablation pair
        scored on the frozen bench.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p class="api-status">status: contract_only · adapters_trained: 0 · claims_without_receipts: 0</p>
  </div>
</section>
